Q5)Enable actuator services and play around few endpoints it exposes.

To enable Spring Boot Actuator, I added the following dependency in pom.xml:

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-actuator</artifactId>
</dependency>

Then, I enabled actuator endpoints by modifying the application.properties file:

management.endpoints.web.exposure.include=*

After running the application, I accessed the following Actuator endpoints:

/actuator/health : Checked application health status.
/actuator/info : Displayed application information.
/actuator/metrics : Monitored performance metrics.
/actuator/env : Displayed environment properties.
/actuator/mappings : Listed all available API routes.